This member of The Listings Lab KILLED it with her niche 🔥

So many agents still get niching wrong, and that’s why I’ll never stop talking about this…

Your niche isn’t a ZIP code.

So it’s time to say buh-bye to geo-farming and hello to niching down by demographic or life transition!

Picking a niche doesn’t have to be complicated.

I always recommend picking a demographic you’re already familiar with.

That way, you’ll know how to relate to them and create content that draws them in.

Our Listings Lab member did exactly that.

Being a former lawyer, she knew exactly how corporate, type-A women were wired.

 So she created a system that was designed to suit their every need.

It was like magic ✨

Her business exploded nearly overnight.
Creating content was effortless because she knew exactly who she was speaking to.

People started finding her through her online content - and referrals were flowing.

Every corporate woman was telling all of her friends about their incredible realtor - who was their new favorite person.

THIS is what we mean when we talk about a signature system!

Want to learn how to create an offer that’s absolutely irresistible to your clients like our member did?

Comment “SYSTEM” below and I’ll send you my free training on creating your signature offer as a real estate agent 👇

Here’s your daily reminder to OWN YOUR WEIRD ✌️⁠
⁠
Business becomes so much more liberating…and FUN…when you allow yourself to show up as YOU.⁠
⁠
…𝘙𝘢𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘳 than some carbon copy of every other agent out there!⁠
⁠
Use me as your example…⁠
⁠
I certainly don’t look like your typical real estate coach.⁠
⁠
I’m a crazy cat lady.⁠
⁠
I’m obsessed with my husband.⁠
⁠
I always have hair in a messy bun.⁠
⁠
But you know what?⁠
⁠
I’m me.⁠
⁠
Unapologetically showing up as your true self is the breath of fresh air your audience needs.⁠
⁠
So if you’re ready to go from generic 👉memorable, ask yourself:⁠
⁠
🤔What makes me different?⁠
🤔What do I want to be known for?⁠
🤔What are my values?⁠
🤔What are my quirks?⁠
⁠
And make sure you’re weaving those things into your social media content!⁠
⁠
Let me know in the comments if you’re ready to ditch the “perfect real estate agent” facade and build an authentic personal brand 👇⁠
.⁠
.⁠

.⁠

The #1 Sales Mistake So Many Agents Make…👇

They shy away from client objections. 

It usually goes something like this…

You’re doing a listing presentation, and as you finish up and begin talking about working together more seriously, you can sense some hesitation.

It’s natural to want to ignore situations that make either us or the client uncomfortable.

But trust me…this is the wrong move ❌

Instead, you want to confront the objection head-on. 
Don’t ignore the objection or pretend it isn’t there. This only gives it more power!

Address the elephant in the room 🐘 

When you say that you understand that there’s some trust that needs to be built here, you can not only acknowledge the elephant…

…but also escort it out.

Want to learn our proven 5-step formula for overcoming client objections, every single time? 

Head to the link in my bio to read the latest post on The Listings Lab Blog, 5 Crucial Steps To Become A Master At Objection Handling In Real Estate 🔗

Who else thinks the hustle-and-grind mentality has to go? 🙋‍♀️ ⁠

Not everything is as it seems! 

You can ROI on your time investment too if your strategy is right.

We are pretty spontaneous people and we’ve made some fun, (albeit a little rash!) decisions in our life together 😅

After we got engaged we were eating at a Chinese restaurant on Spadina. We were chatting about some friends of ours who we heard got ring tattoos after their marriage 💍

We thought to ourselves...

 “That sounds kinda cool…let’s do it!”

Literally, 10 minutes later we found a tattoo parlor down the street and were in line to get tattoos on our ring fingers! 

Mine is a Y (for Yves obvi) that now looks a little like an R, a little like a Y, and a little like a blob. His tattoo says Jessica in my handwriting and is standing the test of time much better than mine!

I love that we do things on a whim. We follow our hearts and do what feels right all the time!

This business is such a labour of love.

And it all started because we felt passionately about sharing my knowledge (and my mistakes) and building our dreams. Together every step of the way 💗

What’s the most spontaneous thing you have ever done? Comment below!

STOP playing it safe in your content! 🛑⁠
⁠
If you feel like you’re struggling to stand out on social media…⁠
⁠
It’s probably because you’re not saying anything very interesting 🤷‍♀️⁠
⁠
I say this with love!⁠
YOU are interesting.⁠
⁠
But filling your social media feed with:⁠
⁠
👉Constant “just listed, just sold” posts⁠
👉Market stats you plugged into a Canva infographic template⁠
👉And the same recycled, corporate-looking headshots⁠
⁠
Is only making your ideal client’s eyes glaze over…⁠
⁠
A strong real estate personal brand produces a sort of brand evangelism. ⁠
⁠
But you’ll never be able to achieve that if you’re always trying to play it safe in your content. ⁠
⁠
You have to be willing to offend some people if you want to attract YOUR people.⁠
⁠
To tune into your polarizing opinions, ask yourself…⁠
⁠
🤔What do I do that’s different than other agents or people in my niche?⁠
⁠
And lean into the controversy! ⁠
⁠
Let me know…⁠
⁠
What’s a polarizing opinion you have about the real estate industry? (My answer is in the comments!)⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

5 Steps To Handle Any Objection A Client Throws Your Way 👉 SWIPE and save this post to reference for your next listing presentation!⁠
⁠
Do client objections make you feel awkward?⁠
⁠
It’s normal to want to avoid objections and continue on without addressing the elephant in the room…⁠
⁠
We may take objections from our clients personally.⁠
⁠
Or we might be so afraid to come off as “pushy” that we ignore our clients’ objections altogether.⁠
⁠
But whatever you do, the worst possible thing is to just pretend the objection isn’t happening.⁠
⁠
The key to objection handling in real estate is not being afraid of the objections…⁠
⁠
 Or shy away from them.⁠
Instead, use our formula 👇⁠
1️⃣ Acknowledge⁠
2️⃣ Accept⁠
3️⃣ Shut Up⁠
4️⃣ Pinpoint The Pain Point⁠
5️⃣ Close⁠
⁠
I want to know…how comfortable are you handling objections on a scale of 1-10? (1 being they make me SO squirmy…and 10 being they don’t phase you at all 💁‍♀️)⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

People don’t want to read the same, boring, market stats.⁠

They want to read about YOU!⁠
⁠
As the saying goes, “People buy people”⁠
⁠
And this couldn’t be truer in real estate.⁠
⁠
You need to create INTIMACY with your ideal clients.⁠
⁠
The secret to doing this is embracing personal content ❤️⁠
⁠
Here are some questions to get your personal content going:⁠
⁠
👉 What are your personal beliefs?⁠
👉 What is your personal philosophy?⁠
👉 What is your story?⁠

When you weave the answers to these questions into your online content…⁠

Your potential clients will connect with you on an EMOTIONAL level!⁠

People make decisions with emotion first, and logic second.⁠

❤️My heart SANK as their eyes glazed over…⁠
⁠
I could tell I was losing them.⁠
⁠
I was young, nervous, and sitting in a million-dollar home across from a couple, going through one of my first listing presentations. ⁠
⁠
The wife seemed mildly interested, but kept zoning out. ⁠
⁠
And the husband had barely taken his eyes off his Blackberry. ⁠
⁠
In a moment, I realized everything I’d been taught about how to do listing presentations felt SO wrong.⁠
⁠
A big-name brokerage trained me in their framework. They taught us how to talk at clients. We were told to stand up, as if we were presenting to a room full of people. ⁠
⁠
As I could feel my potential clients dozing off, I realized…⁠
⁠
I needed to forget everything I’d been taught and do what felt right.⁠
⁠
Instead of standing and lecturing them, I took a deep breath—and then I sat on the sofa with them. ⁠
⁠
Instead of working off a script, I spoke from my heart ❤️⁠
⁠
I started asking them personal questions about the home. ⁠
⁠
👉Why did they buy their house in the first place?⁠
👉What were the things they loved most about it?⁠
👉 What was motivating them to sell it now?⁠
In an instant, the entire dynamic of the conversation shifted.⁠
⁠
Their eyes came alive.⁠
⁠
They started telling me stories about their home.⁠
⁠
And for the first time, we had a real conversation. ⁠
⁠
After that experience, the way I did listing presentations forever changed.⁠
⁠
Now, I don’t even call them listing presentations anymore.⁠
⁠
Instead, we coach our members in The Listings Lab on how to have listing conversations. ⁠
⁠
Who else agrees that it’s time to ditch the old-school listings presentation method and instead focus on true connection with our clients? 🙌⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

When agents say this, I get a little fed up…

“I’d love to build a bigger business…but I value my time too much”

Or:

“I’d love to scale…but my family comes first”

Whaaat?

Who said a bigger business meant LESS time for yourself and your family?

Both of these ideas are FALLACIES.

Building a multi-6 or 7-figure real estate business does NOT require you to:

❌Spend MORE time on the phone with leads
❌Give up precious moments with your loved ones
❌ Constantly choose work over your passions

The whole reason I created The Listings Lab was to show you that you can build a real estate business that doesn’t take over your life.

Take it from me…or any of our successful members.

You often work a LOT harder making 100k a year than making 500k or 1 million.

Why?

Because once you get past early six figures…you HAVE to start embracing systems, automation, and delegation.

You simply have no choice. 

You won’t be able to sustain that amount of volume without those foundations in place!

Have you ever equated more money with harder work or long hours? 

Let me know in the comments if you’re ready to change this mindset!
.
.
.
.
.

Your clients don’t care about your process!⁠
⁠
They only care about how your process will get them RESULTS.⁠
⁠
Think about it this way…⁠
⁠
Let’s say you’re looking to book your vacation with a travel agency 🏝⁠
⁠
When you go to a travel agent, they don’t focus on HOW they’ll get you to your dream destination.⁠
⁠
They don’t tell you how they’re going to stick you in an aluminum tube, throw you through the sky, invite you to share a bathroom with three hundred strangers, and feed you terrible food! 😅⁠
⁠
That’s not what people want to hear about.⁠
⁠
Travel agents sell the destination—that resort in Mexico on the front of the brochure—not the airplane. ⁠
⁠
But so many agents are selling the airplane ✈️⁠
⁠
They go into their listing presentation SO focused on selling the process…⁠
⁠
When all potential clients really want to know is whether or not you can get them to where they want to go. ⁠
⁠
So here’s a quick fix for your next listing presentation 👇⁠
⁠
Stop focusing so much on the nuts and bolts of your offer.⁠
⁠
Instead of telling them every tiny feature and nuance of how your process works…⁠
⁠
Showcase how your process has gotten incredible results for your past clients!⁠
⁠
And I promise you’ll close more deals.⁠
⁠
Let me know in the comments….have you ever been guilty of selling the airplane as a real estate agent? ⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

My most unconventional business advice 👇⁠
⁠
I talk a lot about business and marketing strategy on here, but there’s another big factor when it comes to your success…⁠
⁠
And that’s your ENERGY ⚡⁠
⁠
People want to be around high-vibe people. People are attracted to those who vibrate at a higher frequency. ⁠
⁠
Yes, you may think that sounds a little “woo”...but it’s true.⁠
⁠
If you’re excited about your services, other people will be too. ⁠
⁠
If you’re passionate in your content, other people will want to tune in. ⁠
⁠
You have to genuinely love what you do. ⁠
⁠
I have so much fun running The Listings Lab. And my community can feel it!⁠
⁠
We're all human lie detectors.⁠
⁠
If someone’s faking their enthusiasm, we’re able to feel it.⁠
⁠
If you’re not having fun in your real estate business, something needs to change!⁠
⁠
It might be because you’re running yourself into the ground.⁠
⁠
Or because you hate cold-calling…but you're forcing yourself to do it every day.⁠
⁠
Whatever the case, it’s time to take charge and build a business that actually fills your cup!⁠
⁠
Are you ready? Leave a 🙌 in the comments if you want to make your business fun again 💃💃⁠

The lesson that’s worth the ENTIRE investment in The Listings Lab (it’s not what you think)...⁠
⁠
If you’ve been on a call with me before, you’ve probably heard me say “and then we have PR. Honestly, this is worth the price of The Listings Lab alone.”⁠
⁠
PR is one of the most important things you can do to build your credibility as an agent, whether you’re new or you’re doing 200 deals a year.⁠
⁠
And it’s the thing that no agent is really doing well.⁠
⁠
I didn’t even put this lesson together.⁠
⁠
But I know when to defer to an expert…Ashley, our COO, and Head of Product and Mentorship, is the voice on this lesson and she is the BEST at PR.⁠
⁠
She owned a PR agency before joining our team, and personally got clients in Inc., Forbes, Entrepreneur, Vogue, The Today Show, Allure, HGTV, and over 200 other places.⁠
⁠

There are 3 BIG shifts you need to make to go from low 6 figures to multi-6 or 7 figures…(SAVE this post!)⁠
⁠
👉 Shift 1: Manual Vs. Automation.⁠
Too many entrepreneurs go the route of paying an admin $25/hour to come into the office to perform a task that they could just be paying a software $25/month to do. Wherever you can, leverage automation before outsourcing.⁠
⁠
👉Shift 2: Attraction Vs. Chasing⁠
If you want to be a top real estate agent that closes deals left, right, and center - it’s time to switch from a 1-1 model to a 1-many model. ⁠
⁠
Yes, real estate is a relationship-based business. You need to be having conversations with your ideal clients.⁠
⁠
But not every conversation needs to be one-to-one. ⁠
⁠
👉Shift 3: Solo Agent Vs. Real Estate Team⁠
⁠
When I talk about how to build a real estate team, a lot of people think I just mean hiring an assistant.⁠
⁠
And while that’s a good place to start, I saw the most growth when I started delegating outcomes to people on my team. ⁠
⁠
It’s not enough to simply pass tasks off to team members. You need to cultivate a team of leaders who will help make decisions for you.⁠
⁠
Otherwise, you will always be the bottleneck.⁠
⁠
Let me know in the comments which one of these shifts will you be working on in 2023!⁠

You NEED Core Values To Build A 7-Figure Business…Here’s Why 👇

1️⃣They Eliminate Decision Fatigue
Core values give you a framework to make decisions in your business. By knowing what you stand for as a business, you can base your decisions on those values. 

2️⃣They Help You Lead Your Team Objectively 
When you measure performance on whether someone’s embodying the company’s core values – RATHER than how you think/feel about their performance – you’re acting from a place of clarity rather than ambiguity. (Which is more helpful for everyone!)

3️⃣They Help You Hire & Fire
Hiring can be overwhelming, but when you have core values in place, you have a foundation for the type of person you’re looking for. On the other hand, they also help you understand when a team member is no longer acting in alignment with your company’s values.

More is NOT always more…⁠
⁠
If you’ve had a call with me, then you’ve likely heard this story before, but in July of 2017 I was in Maui with my gorgeous hubby and we were having the best time.⁠
⁠
I felt happier and freer than I had in years.⁠
⁠
We were driving along the highway, wind in my hair and Despacito blasting…⁠
⁠
All of a sudden I was bawling. Like sobbing uncontrollably.⁠
⁠
What was wrong with me? I had EVERYTHING I’d ever wanted.⁠
⁠
I looked over at Yves and just spit it out, “I don’t want to sell real estate anymore.”⁠
⁠
STUNNED SILENCE.⁠
⁠
We spent the next few months talking about what this would mean, which also meant me hitting my journal like a madman.⁠
⁠
I processed, I wrote, I worked through things, I cried, I found clarity...it was one of the most emotional times of my life. I was terrified.⁠
⁠
What I realized through all of this though was that money isn’t the goal.⁠
⁠
Once I got to the point where I didn’t need more money, I quickly saw that I wasn’t living the way I wanted to...I wasn’t serving the people I felt passionate about.⁠
⁠
So I did the scariest and riskiest thing I’ve ever done...I started again. I started a new business from scratch.⁠
⁠
Out of this clarity was born The Listings Lab, which is my signature program helping agents scale through automated quality lead generation…⁠
⁠
Money TRULY doesn’t make you happy. I had built the dream...or what seemed like someone else’s dream and it felt empty.⁠
⁠
I chased fulfillment and it changed the whole direction of my life.⁠
⁠
Whatever you do in your life, make sure you’re chasing the right thing...is it easy to make money in real estate? Sure, but if you’re not connected to what you’re doing, eventually you’ll end up where I was.⁠
⁠
Do what you love. Love what you do.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

I have 2 tattoos that I used to think I had to cover to be successful.⁠
⁠
I tried to play the part and be as professional as possible. Guess what?⁠
⁠
I ended up with a business that didn’t feel like me and I eventually got sick of putting on the “mask” every day.⁠
⁠
So I stopped pretending or hiding a side of me that is true.⁠
⁠
I don’t have a lot of tattoos, although I’m always thinking of another one…⁠
⁠
My first one I got when I was 16. I still love it just as much as I did then. It was very intentional.⁠
⁠
It says “Nana” because my Nana was my rock. I still talk to her whenever I need to feel her. She was the funniest, most sarcastic woman and holy smokes did she love me….in a way that I didn’t understand until I got older and could look back at it.⁠
⁠
I carry her with me and this tattoo doesn’t face out, it faces me because it’s only for me.⁠
⁠
My second tattoo is mostly hidden. It’s on my ring finger and hides under my wedding and engagement rings. It’s a simple “y” that now looks more like a blob:)⁠
⁠
This one was spur of the moment. Yves and I were walking down Spadina (Chinatown in Toronto) and we passed a tattoo parlour...we walked in and both got one.⁠
⁠
His says Jessica in my handwriting down his ring finger. I still love my y blob...it brings me back to that day and how crazy in love we were. We still are.⁠
⁠
About 6 years ago I stopped hiding my tattoos. Nothing changed. So I stopped hiding “Jess” and my business boomed. Even people who met me for the first time always got the real me.⁠
⁠
Authenticity can be felt. People want to know you, not the image that you try to keep intact.⁠
⁠
I ended up with a business I liked a lot more and I got to talk about my Nana with people and share what she means to me.⁠
⁠
Win/Win!⁠
.⁠

I still remember trying to calm my racing heart as I picked up the phone to call my dad and tell him the news...⁠
⁠
I wasn't expecting him to be happy about it.⁠
⁠
Entrepreneur Magazine was publishing my experience with domestic violence in a feature story. ⁠
⁠
On the one hand, I felt courageous. I knew this story needed to be shared. If I helped just one person who could see themselves in my story, it would be worth it.⁠
⁠
But on the other hand, I felt nervous. I'd never shared my story in such a public way.⁠
⁠
If you didn't know, I'm half-Chinese.⁠
⁠
And my dad?⁠
⁠
He's the typical Chinese doctor.⁠
⁠
Very stoic. Very private. He's not exactly a man who wears his heart on his sleeve...⁠
⁠
I braced myself for a difficult conversation. ⁠
⁠
I was ready to tell him, "This is coming out, whether you like it or not."⁠
⁠
But his response shocked me.⁠
⁠
Instead of critiquing my decision to go public with my story, he commended me.⁠
⁠
He told me he couldn't be more proud.⁠
⁠
He supported me wholeheartedly, telling me he understood just how impactful my story was...⁠
⁠
...and how many people it could help.⁠
⁠
I share this story because I want you to know...⁠
⁠
If my traditional Chinese Dad can find a way to celebrate vulnerability, I know you can too.⁠
⁠
You might be worried about what people will think if you get vulnerable in your online content.⁠
⁠
Your family, your friends, your ex, or that acquaintance from high school.⁠
⁠
But in reality, the OPPOSITE happens.⁠
⁠
People don't judge you...⁠
⁠
They admire you.⁠
⁠
So have the courage to tell your story.⁠
⁠
Because the impact it could have is far greater than you know! ❤️⁠
⁠

They will LITERALLY tell you what to say if you ask the right questions and listen.

⁠
So ask yourself...⁠
⁠
⁠
What are the emotions your client is experiencing that are fueling the move?⁠

⁠
Say you're serving “upsizers.”⁠

⁠
It's one thing to understand that they're outgrowing their space.⁠
⁠
⁠
But it's another to understand how that's showing up in their everyday lives...⁠
⁠
⁠
👉 Maybe they're fighting every day because they’re tripping over the kids’ toys⁠
⁠
⁠
👉 Maybe they're feeling resentful of their loved ones because they're 4 people sharing the same bathroom⁠
⁠
⁠
👉 Maybe they know they need to move, but they're scared to cut emotional ties with the house their kids grew up in ⁠
⁠

If you go into a listing conversation with that level of understanding and empathy?⁠

Here's the sad truth... There are TONS more “keyboard warriors” sitting at home than ever before.⁠
⁠
⁠
And unfortunately, that means...⁠
⁠
⁠
More mean comments. More mean emails. More negativity online.⁠
⁠
⁠
But you know what else it means?⁠
⁠
⁠
More eyes on your content. More attention possibilities. More love!⁠
⁠
⁠
The thing that I want you to know is that what someone else says to you or about you online has NOTHING to do with you.⁠
⁠
⁠
This took me a long time to come to terms with. It used to bother me. I’d get a pit in my stomach and want to crawl into a hole.⁠
⁠
⁠
And even though I've come to accept that trolls come with the territory, it doesn't mean I never have hard days.⁠
⁠
⁠
Just a few weeks ago, the launch of my new ads was met with a slew of online hate from men commenting on my appearance...saying that I "didn't look good enough" to get agents to 7 figures. ⁠
⁠
⁠
But here's what I tell myself in these moments:⁠
⁠
⁠
These types of insults have nothing to do with me.⁠
⁠
⁠
They’re just projections.⁠
⁠
⁠
I have this visualization that I’ve been doing. I close my eyes and imagine this person handing me their “crap” and then I say, “no, thanks! This is yours, not mine.”⁠
⁠
⁠
Do you have any tips on how you deal with trolls online?⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

Being able to show them what’s possible is so much more powerful than selling the transaction.⁠

⁠

This ONE thing will save you hours and hours when onboarding new agents...

I’m talking about your Real Estate Operations Manual or Playbook.

Also known as your set of SOPs (Standard Operating Procedures). 

SOPs are like detailed recipe books for your business tasks 👩‍🍳

They make it easy for any team member to do a task correctly every time, saving you time and money 💰

Here’s the basic template all your real estate SOPs should follow 👇

➡️ The Basics
Use a simple template with a title, date, department name, and owner of the document. Include when the document was last updated and link any required resources.

➡️ Clear Action Steps 
Include clear action steps that are accurate or that apply to 95 percent of cases. Unclear SOPs will only leave you bogged down with questions, as your team will constantly be clarifying your instructions. 

Take the time to make them detailed and unambiguous if you truly want to save time!

➡️ How To Know When The Job Is Done
Help team members know when the job is done by giving clear markers and checklists. They should have a clear understanding of what constitutes a job well done!

If getting your SOPs done is on your priority list (and it SHOULD be!) save this post to come back to!

Raise your hand in the comments if SOPs have been a lifesaver for your real estate business too 🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️🙋‍♀️

.
.

3 Types of Posts You NEED To Create To Get Inbound Leads Off Social Media 👇

🤓An Authority-Building Post

An authority-building post helps showcase your expertise to your potential clients. 

Think about content that educates and delivers value, as well as shows off your signature process. Your signature process is how you help clients get from point A to point B.

This type of post will help you become the go-to agent in your client’s mind.

Honest question: do you actually love “keeping things small”? Or are you just terrified of more responsibility?

For years, I prided myself on the fact that I was a “lone wolf”. 

I told myself that being able to do it all on my own was one of my biggest strengths. 

I liked being self-sufficient, and always in control.

But in reality?

These tendencies were my biggest downfall.

Thinking I was better off alone was just a story I made up to protect myself.

Because deep down, I was too afraid to trust anyone else. 

So many agents subconsciously hold themselves back because they’re terrified of having to be responsible for other people. 

As a solo agent, if you fail, the only person you have to answer to is yourself.

👉 You’re responsible for making decisions that will be in everyone’s best interest

And yes, keeping your business small can feel good. It feels comfortable. 

But sooner or later, you’ll hit a wall.

The question is...

Have you ever been talking to a lead, asking them ALL THE THINGS about their property…and then the conversation just…fizzles out?⁠
⁠
This happens to agents ALL the time.⁠
⁠
Quite frankly, you’re boring the person on the other side of the conversation. ⁠
⁠
So what can you do instead?⁠
⁠

⁠
People LOVE to talk about themselves, especially their personal lives. ⁠
⁠
They adore discussing their kids, their families, their hobbies, and their passions.⁠
⁠
So, instead of questioning them about what kind of property they're hunting for, try getting personal.⁠
⁠
Instead of just focusing on property features, seek to understand the 'why' behind their move. ⁠

Is it for a career transition? More space for a growing family? A fresh start?⁠

By learning more about their life transitions, you go from being another agent who's pestering them with questions so they can gain their business…⁠

⁠
“I’ll just wait UNTIL X, Y, Z”⁠
⁠

The moment I realized my priorities were ALL wrong...

I still remember when I was an agent stuck on the 6-figure hamster wheel.

I was making enough to maintain my lifestyle.

Back then, I needed the designer bags and luxury shopping sprees.

But...

I had no time at all.

For myself.

For my loved ones.

For the moments that REALLY mattered. 

I can still remember when I was slapped across the face with the fact that my priorities were seriously EFFED up!⠀

If you’ve been around here for a while you’ve heard this story before…⠀

I was sitting at dinner with my husband (then fiance). We had booked this in as “date night” and it was special and important that we spend that quality time together.⠀

My phone was on the table right next to my knife. My fingers reach to it.⠀

It buzzed. I spit my food into my napkin and walked out of the room to answer it.⠀

It was nothing urgent...just one of the 500 leads I called that day, returning my call to tell me he wasn’t interested.

When I walked back into the room, I saw Yves sitting alone. Looking broken. 

I looked up at him and thought, “What am I doing?”⠀

I fought hard for this relationship. It was SO important to me and I was sabotaging it.⠀

Sure, I could buy the purse, but if I couldn’t show up for the person I loved on the night that was supposed to be just for us...

Why did it matter? 

It was at that moment that I knew something needed to change. 

Since then, time freedom and being able to show up for my loved ones became my #1 priority. 

So be honest with me in the comments...

Does your current business model allow you to show up for the people who mean the most?
.
.
.
.
.

This is your wake-up call....

We need to stop viewing always “being busy” as a badge of honor.

The “always-on”, hustling agent image is revered - but WHY? 

Since when did being a realtor become synonymous with being a martyr?

Why do we always see putting our clients first as the pinnacle of “goodness” in a real estate business?⠀

When in reality, it only means we’re putting ourselves and our loved ones LAST.

It’s time that this ridiculous idea of the “always available” Realtor ends…⠀

Do you call your doctor on Saturday night when you have a headache? 

Nope.

Every other business has hours and boundaries and allows for real freedom.⠀

If you’re a real estate martyr you have none of that.⠀

Who else thinks it’s time we stop joking about 80-hour work weeks and going on family vacations chained to our laptops...

And start ACTUALLY making a change towards a more sustainable business model?

Leave a 🙌 in the comments if you’re with me!
.
.
.
.
.

I almost didn't recognize my friend... ⁠
⁠
You know how everyone has that one friend who's the life of the party? Quirky, fun, undeniably themselves? ⁠
⁠
That was her. ⁠
⁠
But then she got her real estate license and, almost overnight, her social media persona transformed. ⁠
⁠
Her feeds became a series of stiff, corporate snapshots — her in a suit, arms crossed, and none of her original spark.⁠
⁠
Scrolling through her posts, I felt a sense of sadness. ⁠
⁠
She had lost everything that made her...her. ⁠
⁠
This bubbly, eccentric soul had boxed herself into a mold that just wasn't her. ⁠
⁠
This a trap I see SO many agents fall into…⁠
⁠
They trade in their unique personality and quirks for a carbon-copy corporate real estate Barbie persona.⁠
⁠
But in reality?⁠
⁠
The BEST thing you could do for your business is to be you - authentically you. ⁠
⁠
The ones who find the most success and joy in real estate are those who embrace their authenticity…and build a community that loves them for who they actually are.⁠
⁠
Believe me, the worst thing you can do is create a persona that isn't you. That moment when your followers meet you in person and see a different person? Yeah, that's the real nightmare. ⁠
⁠
So own your weird. Embrace your quirks. Give the world a chance to love you for the real you. ⁠
⁠
I promise - business becomes 100x more fun and easier when you do it that way! ⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
⁠

Let’s talk about the harmful expectation trap so many new agents fall into...

Your friends and family aren’t obligated to be your first clients.

Yes, they love you!

But you have to remember...

This is the biggest investment of their life. 

They’re not going to make a decision like that purely on goodwill.

I bought myself a cake when I got my first troll comment. ⁠
⁠
Why?⁠
⁠
Because I knew it meant that I'd made it.⁠
⁠
I saw it as a celebration.⁠
⁠
My first online hate comment showed me I was polarizing...⁠
⁠
My content was creating a strong emotional reaction in people - whether that was love and appreciation or hatred.⁠
⁠
It reminded me that I was brave enough to share a message that went across the grain. ⁠
⁠
But I didn't always have this mindset. ⁠
⁠
When I first started sharing content on social media, I was terrified people were going to hate me.⁠
⁠
I decided to flip my mindset...⁠
⁠
Now, every time someone on the team sees a clever hate comment, we continue the tradition.⁠
⁠
We screenshot it and share it with the team!⁠
⁠
We've turned it into a fun game. ⁠
⁠
Because at the end of the day, whenever somebody trolls you, it actually has nothing to do with you. ⁠
⁠
And it has everything to do with them. ⁠
⁠
Social media is just a mirror. ⁠
⁠
When people put hateful comments out into the universe, they're actually just telling you more about themselves.⁠
⁠
Let's talk about it in the comments. How do you deal with hate - or the fear of trolls?⁠
⁠
Do you laugh about them, celebrate them, or ignore them altogether?⁠
⁠
Whatever you do...PLEASE don't take them seriously!⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
⁠

Are you making these 4 mistakes with your niche?

👉 Trying to Choose Multiple Niches: Stop spreading yourself too thin by trying to go after multiple niches at once. Start with dominating one niche, and once you’ve established yourself, you can gradually expand into others. 

👉 Thinking You Need To Go After The Biggest/Most Common Niche Possible: Bigger isn’t always better. By narrowing down your niche and serving an ultra-specific audience, you’ll be a ‘big fish in a small pond’. It’ll be easier to quickly rise to the top as the go-to agent for your clients in that niche. 

👉 Choosing A Niche You Don’t Resonate With: Real estate is a people business. Choose a niche that you deeply understand and can effortlessly connect with. This will make your offer and content more magnetic to your ideal clients. For example...if you’re a millennial dog mom, don’t try to go after empty nesters who are looking for a new place after their kids have moved out. 

👉 Thinking A Niche Is A Property Type: Saying “I do condos” or “I do luxury” isn’t a niche. Shift your attention to the type of person you want to serve. Understand their underlying motivation for why they’re looking to make this life transition. People don’t move for fun, so figure out what’s driving their move and get to the heart of the problem. 

Let me know in the comments... what’s your real estate niche?

I've been a perfectionist since I was 10 years old.

My dad was always tough on us. He had high expectations. And my brother was always the 'smart one' in our family. 

I grew up feeling like I had something to prove. 

I still remember the day I had to quit competitive swimming.

When I started swimming, I was only a little girl; my body was still growing. 

Swimming involves a lot of repetitive motion on the joints, and after only four years of competing, I got badly injured, to the point that my shoulder required surgery. 

I had to say goodbye to my competitive swimming dreams.

I bawled my eyes out beside the changing rooms. 

The coach, who had first recruited me to the team, sat next to me. 

I told her that I didn’t know who I was without competing. I felt like it defined me, and I couldn’t imagine doing anything else. 

No 13-year-old should feel that way—but there I was. That pressure to be the best and to do things on my own had come to define my identity.

Years later, when I was working in real estate, not much had changed.

I felt like I defined myself by how many deals a year I did.

By what my commission cheques were.

By how many handbags I could afford.

I defined myself by what people could see externally when on the inside I was suffering. 

But slowly, a shift started to happen.

I started to let others in.

I started to release the pressure I put on myself.

And I started to realize - life isn't all about winning. It's about growing.

Because at the end of the day, I never had anything to prove in the first place.

This is your reminder to redefine your self-worth, not by what you do...but by who you are ❤️

I wonder how many of you can relate? 

How often do you find yourself defining your worth by external factors? 

And I'm curious, what would it look like if you decided to measure your success differently? 

Let me know in the comments 👇

This mindset shift changes everything 👇⁠
⁠
You can read all the marketing books…⁠
⁠
You can binge all of the podcasts…⁠
⁠
You can keep up with all of the latest trends…⁠
⁠
But if you don’t have the right perspective when it comes to real estate marketing, your strategy will always fall flat.⁠
⁠
A helpful idea to master your marketing mindset is the idea of jab, jab, jab, right hook.⁠
⁠
This concept was coined by Gary Vee back in 2013, but the principles remain extremely relevant to this day.⁠
⁠
In jab, jab, jab, right hook, the jabs are every instance you provide value to your ideal clients.⁠
⁠
This includes:⁠
⁠
👉 The valuable content you put out⁠
⁠
👉 The appreciation you show your people⁠
⁠
👉 The kind gestures you do for your community.⁠
⁠
The right hook, on the other hand, is the ask.⁠
⁠
It may be:⁠
⁠
👉 Asking for a sale⁠
⁠
👉 Asking for a referral⁠
⁠
👉 Asking for registration on an ad⁠
⁠
What jab, jab, jab, right hook stands for is essentially give, give, give then ask.⁠
⁠
Your marketing has to be FAR more centered on giving to your audience rather than just selling to them.⁠
⁠
The advertising industry has changed drastically and the old ways of marketing are out.⁠
⁠
I’d go as far as to say that in 2023, the model might even look more like jab, jab, jab, jab, jab, jab…right hook.⁠
⁠
When you give and give and give, then the ask is ALWAYS going to be more successful.⁠
⁠
Leave a 🙌 in the comments if you’re with me!⁠

The balancing act of the Realtor.⁠
⁠
Doing all the things?⁠
⁠
Schedule? What schedule?⁠
⁠
The number one question I get asked is what an agent should be doing on a daily basis.⁠
⁠
Answer? Not what you want to hear.⁠
⁠
It depends.⁠
⁠
There's no one cookie-cutter way to run your business (don't listen to the people that tell you there is.)⁠
⁠
If you're a single agent trying to grow it'll be different than someone with a team.⁠
⁠
If you have an admin it'll be different than if you don't.⁠
⁠
On top of this, your strengths will impact what you do and what someone else does for you.⁠
⁠
You have to know how to do it all, but you don't necessarily have to do ALL the things every single day.⁠
⁠
I put a little exercise in my Facebook Group. It's a task audit.⁠
⁠
Here's how it works to get you clear:⁠
⁠
1. Write down everything you do on a daily basis for 7 days straight (use a typical week if you have one) and how much time you’re spending on each task.⁠
⁠
Be super honest about everything…how many times you check your email in a day, etc⁠
⁠
2. Now highlight everything that you believe that only you can do. Be careful here. No egos allowed. Seriously, for your business, what can only you do?⁠
⁠
3. Now make 4 columns on a piece of paper. Label: mine, eliminate, automate, outsource⁠
⁠
4. Put each and every task into one of those columns. Think carefully about each one and ask yourself in this order…Can it be eliminated? If not, Can it be automated? If not, can it be outsourced? ⁠
⁠
Only what’s left goes into your column (mine).⁠
⁠
5. Once you have everything in those 4 columns you can start to tackle each column one at a time. ⁠
⁠
Let me know in the comments if you're going to try this 👇⁠

What's the BEST social platform to be on right now? ⁠
⁠
☝️This is probably the #1 question people ask me.⁠
⁠
First off...it'd be impossible to answer this question for you right off the bat.⁠
⁠
Because the answer is always...it depends.⁠
⁠
When it comes to choosing the perfect platform for your content, it all boils down to your niche and target audience. ⁠
⁠
You want to dominate the platform where your ideal clients are spending most of their time.⁠
⁠
So if you're serving retirees, or seniors who are downsizing, don't pour all of your energy into LinkedIn which has a primarily professional audience.⁠
⁠
Direct your energy and efforts to where your potential clients ACTUALLY spend their time!⁠
⁠
But SECOND of all...⁠
⁠
Obsessing over what platform you need to be seen on is the wrong focus altogether. ⁠
⁠
The reality is, I've seen agents have success on Facebook, TikTok, Instagram, LinkedIn, or even YouTube.⁠
⁠
So the question isn't necessarily "What platform should I show up on?" but instead:⁠
⁠
"How can I RETAIN people's attention on the platform I've chosen?"⁠
⁠
Because no matter what platform you choose, everyone has the same goal...⁠
⁠
To retain people's attention for as long as they can so people stay on their platform, LONGER.⁠
⁠
When you know how to get people's attention, you're rewarded by social media algorithms - your posts get more reach and engagement.⁠

Try This Simple Trick To Sign More Clients From Your Listing Conversations 👇⁠
⁠
Listen more, talk less!⁠
⁠
Note that I said 'listing conversation', not 'presentation'. ⁠
⁠
This isn't about trying to impress your clients with a well-rehearsed pitch or a chance to talk their ear off about how great you are. ⁠
⁠
Why do we call it a presentation when it should be a 2-way conversation? ⁠
⁠
Why are we taught to talk AT our clients instead of TO them?⁠
⁠
If you want to sign more clients, it's time to let them do the talking.⁠
⁠
In real estate, we often feel the need to fill the silence, to sell ourselves, to convince. ⁠
⁠
But the real magic happens when we let our clients take the lead. ⁠
⁠
When we ask the right questions and truly listen to their hopes, dreams, fears, and desires.⁠
⁠
I still remember the day this clicked for me.⁠
⁠
I saw my clients' eyes glazing over as I gave my presentation...so I decided to put my fancy deck away and sat down on the couch with them instead. ⁠
⁠
I stopped 'presenting' and started listening.⁠
⁠
All of a sudden, I had their attention.⁠
⁠
You see, selling shouldn't be about giving your clients what YOU think they need.⁠
⁠
It should be about taking the time to truly listen to their problem, and then figuring out whether or not your service can solve that problem.⁠
⁠
Imagine a doctor that prescribed drugs without listening to their patient's symptoms.⁠
⁠
That's what it's like when you pitch someone without taking the time to get to know them and what they're going through!⁠
⁠
So talk less, listen more, and start asking better questions.⁠
⁠
Who else thinks it's time to turn listing presentations into listing conversations? Let me know in the comments if you're with me 👇⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

Stop building a business you hate.⁠

I’ve seen it happen far too many times.⁠

⁠Agents taking advice and adding on a bunch of things to their plate that they think they “should” do…⁠

⁠…but that only leaves them burnt out, miserable, and exhausted.⁠

⁠Before I add ANYTHING into my business, I ask myself two questions.⁠

1️⃣ Is it unlimitedly scalable? ⁠

2️⃣ Do I enjoy it? ⁠

If the answer is no to either of those things, it’s not happening.⁠

⁠I don’t add anything to my plate that isn’t required for growth and doesn’t bring me joy or fulfillment.⁠

At the end of the day, you’re building YOUR business. ⁠

So stop doing stuff you *think* is necessary, or because you *think* it’s what you *should* be doing. ⁠

⁠Because when you dig deeper, you realize that a lot of these 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘶𝘭𝘥𝘴 aren’t adding to your bottom line... they’re just wasting your energy. ⁠

Your energy is everything as a CEO, so, please…⁠

⁠Don’t waste it building a business that you hate. ⁠

⁠Who’s with me? Leave a 🙌 if you agree!⁠

People don't work with logos.⁠

⁠
Which is why you NEED to be the face of your brand.⁠

⁠

These posts feel impersonal, monotonous, and they're overused.⁠
⁠
👉 Instead, people want to hear about your story. What made you get into real estate in the first place?⁠
⁠
👉 People want to hear your vulnerability. What's something that's challenged you in the past - and how did you overcome it?⁠
⁠
👉 People want to hear your wins. Not in a braggy way, but in a human way. What are you really proud of yourself for? It doesn't even have to be real estate related. It could be the pride you feel as a father, or the gratitude you feel for the way you and your spouse work together in your marriage.⁠

Clients are searching for authenticity, not perfection. They resonate with real experiences, genuine emotions, and most importantly, they want to know the real YOU!⁠

Are you ready to stop hiding behind your business' page and embrace the personal brand? ⁠

But I knew I needed to act quickly.⁠
⁠
👉 I was forced to rebuild my real estate business from nothing.⁠
⁠

⁠
And from there, we were able to scale it to seven figures…⁠
⁠
In just six months.⁠
⁠
One of the biggest superpowers of successful business owners is they do not hesitate when it comes to financial decisions.⁠
⁠
When you hesitate to invest, your unwillingness to ACT will kill your momentum.⁠
⁠

When My Friend Did THIS, It Felt Like A Punch To The Gut...

I have a good friend who has a health and fitness business and we talk back and forth almost every day…⁣

Here’s what happened to me a few weeks ago…⁣

One day we were talking about my fitness goals...I was just chatting away and sharing with her as a friend…⁣

Then BOOM! She pitched me.⁣

I can’t even describe how it felt. It felt like being punched.⁣

It’s been a few weeks and I haven’t felt like reaching out to chat. Things feel weird.⁣

It felt like she crossed a line and it felt really yucky.⁣

I see this happen in real estate all of the time too.

From the get-go, as agents, It's what we've been taught. 

I'm sure you've been told that you can’t be a “secret agent” and that you have to get comfortable asking your friends and family for business.⁣

But here's the thing...

It gets tiring real quick - and starts to leave a sour taste in people's mouths. 

Just like it did in mine when my friend turned a personal chat into a pitch.

People don't want to feel like you're always wanting something from them. 

Your friends, past clients, and family don’t want to be asked for referrals all the time. 

They may be too polite to tell you - but I'm not going to sugarcoat things.

Referrals that come freely are one thing...but asking for them all the time isn’t helping you.⁣

People used to do this because we couldn't easily bring in new clients like we can now with digital marketing.

Those days are LONG gone...like 10 years gone. As marketing gets more sophisticated we have better and better tools to attract the clients we want.⁣

So leave your business cards at home and go have lunch with a friend...because they’re your friend...

NOT because you need a touchpoint. 🤷🏻‍♀️

Has a friend ever pitched you before when you weren't asking for it? Did it leave an icky taste in your mouth? Let me know if you've ever had something go down like this in the comments 👇
.
.
.
.
.

This Real Estate Branding Mistake Could Cost You Thousands...

When you think of “branding” - do you think about the visual elements of your brand? Logos, fonts, color palettes, and patterns?

A lot of people do.

Often, the first thing agents do when they’re getting serious about building their brand is to invest in a branding agency. 

They think once they get their brand mood board, logo, fonts, and colors, they’ll be good to go.

This couldn’t be further from the truth. 

Sure, a well-designed logo and an appealing color scheme might make your brand visually memorable...

But at the end of the day, you’re barely scratching the surface.

True branding goes a whole lot deeper. 

Your brand is how people perceive you when you’re not in the room. 

It’s about your reputation, the quality of your service, and the consistency in your messaging.

Don’t make the mistake of pouring thousands of dollars into your visual branding before getting clear on the foundational aspects.

These aesthetic pieces can come later. 

Trust me, I’ve seen 7-figure businesses who’ve designed their logo in Canva.

Your color scheme or fonts are NOT going to make or break your business.

Maybe it was:
👉 Joining a mentorship program
👉 Hiring your first team member
👉 Or hitting ‘publish’ on that video...

We often obsess over ‘ROI’ (Return on Investment). But have you ever considered the ‘COI’? The Cost of Inaction? 
 Every moment you wait to take action, you’re not just delaying success—you’re incurring a cost. 
 Every delay is potential money, opportunities, and growth left on the table. 
 Remember, ‘Ready’ is a myth. 
 Jumping in might feel risky, but the cost of staying still is far greater.
 No one is ever 100% prepared for change. 
 We have to make peace with that fact and get comfortable with the concept of launching and learning. 
 Business, at its core, is problem-solving. 
 By constantly waiting for the perfect answer, you miss out on discovering the right solution. 
 If fear is in the driver’s seat, stagnation is your destination.
 Break the cycle. Realize that the real cost isn’t in taking risks—it’s in doing nothing.

In one weekend, I did more deals than I did in an entire year. Instead of joy, I felt...lost.⁠
⁠
You'd think it would be cause for celebration, right?⁠
⁠
But honestly, I just felt overwhelmed. I didn’t understand how to process what had just happened. ⁠
⁠
A massive up-leveling had just occurred—and it scared me.⁠
⁠
Here's the thing 👇⁠
⁠
While we often think we're the most afraid of failure, that's often not the case. ⁠
⁠
We know how to handle failure.⁠
⁠
Failure is clear-cut, it usually points us in the exact direction of where something went wrong.⁠
⁠
But success?⁠
⁠
It's murkier. ⁠
⁠
We're uncertain about the exact cause, and that ambiguity can be unnerving.⁠
⁠
Suddenly finding success after consistent struggles feels...foreign.⁠
⁠
It's as if our survival-driven brains see success as a new potential threat. ⁠
⁠
Success can feel so unfamiliar that we unintentionally self-sabotage so that we can go back to what's comfortable.⁠
⁠

They said I'd never be a good leader...⁠
⁠
I got my license through a large, well-known training brokerage (I won’t say names, but you can probably guess). ⁠
⁠
One of the first things they had me do was complete the DISC Personality Test. ⁠
⁠
I wasn't sure what to expect - all I knew was that I was (and am) very introverted.⁠
⁠
I did the test and waited for my results.⁠
⁠
I was young, a little naive, and full of hope and ambition.⁠
⁠
When I got the results... my heart sank.⁠
⁠
Turns out, they labeled me as a non-dominant profile - and implied I wasn't cut out to lead a team.⁠
⁠
In fact, they said I would probably be better suited as an admin. ⁠
⁠
Pretty hilarious considering the work I do now and what I’ve built -- but there was nothing funny about it at the time. ⁠
⁠
It wasn't just the test results that stung...Or the way my brokerage interpreted them...⁠
⁠
It was the way that they made me question my own potential.⁠
⁠
I couldn't help but feel disappointed in myself. ⁠
⁠
But here's the thing...⁠
⁠
Yes, I'm an introvert... but I’m also incredibly stubborn.⁠
⁠
Some may see that as a flaw, but I wear it as a badge of honor. ⁠
⁠
It's that very trait that pushed me to rise above their judgments, carve out my own path, and prove them wrong.⁠
⁠
Always remember...the limitations others set for you get to be your fuel.⁠
⁠
Have you ever been underestimated? Let me know below 👇⁠

⁠
You want to be posting 1/3 personal content, 1/3 authority content, and 1/3 social proof content.⁠

Here's what that looks like in practice: ⁠
⁠

⁠
Talk about your personal beliefs, stories, and behind-the-scenes of your life. Connect on a real, human level.⁠
⁠
2️⃣ Authority-Building Content⁠
⁠
Showcase your expertise and signature process that helps clients from A to B. Become their go-to expert.⁠
⁠
3️⃣ Social Proof Content⁠
⁠
Share testimonials, case studies, and PR that demonstrate how you get big results for happy clients.⁠

I Cried When I Hit 7 Figures...⁠
⁠
Back when I was selling real estate, I finally reached that elusive 7-figure mark.⁠
⁠
Hitting that milestone was supposed to be a celebration. But instead, it was the most miserable and exhausting time of my life.⁠
⁠
I had no team, no systems - just me alone trying to do it all. ⁠
⁠
I'd put on a smile, but inside I was miserable. ⁠
⁠
My phone would ring and I'd cry, handing it off to my husband.⁠
⁠
The praise from others made it harder to be real. ⁠
⁠
I pretended I was thriving, but in reality, I felt trapped by success.⁠
⁠
It took me years of suffering, pretending I was happy because I looked like I was doing well from the outside. ⁠
⁠
But you don't have to.⁠
⁠
You don't have to sacrifice your soul and sanity in order to achieve your goals. ⁠

You can win AND have support. ⁠

Do you have a need to be needed? 

Here’s the thing...

Feeling ‘needed’ by our clients can feel good. It’s a bit of an ego boost, feeling like you’re the ONLY person out there who can help them. 

UNTIL things start to go South. 

What if you need to take extended time off? 

What if you get sick or your husband’s health declines and you need to take care of him? 

This actually happened to one of our members in The Listings Lab. She had no team or systems, and when her husband got sick and she needed to take care of him, her business started to decline. 

Life has a way of throwing us curveballs when we least expect it.

So you need to take a serious look at your business, and ask yourself: 

👉🏼 Is your business life-proof? 

If not, you have a choice to make. 

Do you want to keep feeding your ego account because it makes you feel good to have your clients only depend on you? 

Or do you want to start putting in the work to build a business that can weather the storms of life with you? 

A business that can be your steady anchor when things get tough because you’ve built it with sustainability in mind? 

Let me know in the comments if having a life-proof business is a part of your 2024 vision 👇🏼
.
.
.
.

More money doesn’t automatically mean more freedom!⁠
⁠
There’s no freedom without time.⁠
⁠
If you’re the main (or only) workhorse in your business, then it’s time to build a plan for the future.⁠
⁠
Right now you might be having a blast working in your business every day, but trust me...eventually, you’ll need some space and more time to work ON the business.⁠
⁠
It’s almost impossible to scale and do this all yourself.⁠
⁠
“What if I don’t want to scale?”⁠
⁠
I get it. You want to serve your clients and have relationships with each person...BUT I want you to have a life too.⁠
⁠
You WILL hit a ceiling of what you can do on your own and then what happens if you get sick? This is 100% not to scare you, but to make sure that you’re protecting yourself in the future.⁠
⁠
We had an absolutely wonderful woman in The Listings Lab. She’d been a top-producing agent for years, her clients LOVED her. But a few years ago, her husband got sick and she wanted to take care of him.⁠
⁠
Thankfully he recovered, but it took a few years, which also meant a few years away from her business.⁠
⁠
This hurt them financially.⁠
⁠
This is just one example of why it’s so important to be able to have your business run when you’re not able to run it.⁠
⁠
I want total freedom for you. Not because you need to be able to live a life of leisure (which you should be able to too), but it's because I want to make sure you’re really okay and don’t have to worry about one more thing if life ever throws you a curve ball.⁠
⁠
Tell me ONE THING you would do in the comments if you were able to build a business that actually let you step away 👇🏼⁠

Do you want to be the Chanel or the Walmart of the real estate world?

Because here's the thing...

If I buy a bag from Walmart, I’m heavily focused on the bag itself. 

Essentially, I need something to carry my stuff. Something I can throw my wallet, my keys and my water bottle in. Something to get my stuff from point A to point B.

But if I buy a bag from Chanel, it’s no longer just about the bag. It’s about the experience of buying that bag.

You expect every part of the process to feel luxurious.

Maybe you get a glass of champagne when you enter the store 🥂 Or if you order online, it will be gorgeously wrapped and the unboxing will be an event in and of itself.

Think about what kind of experience you want to give your clients as an agent.

And then act accordingly.

Remember, if you want to have a million-dollar real estate brand, you have to TREAT your business like a million-dollar real estate brand.

❌ Premium real estate brands don’t brag about doing 400 deals a year all over social media.

✔️ Instead, they make their clients feel like they're their only clients. They prioritize their client's experience over everything else.

❌ Premium real estate brands don’t rely on showing off their business to get more business by filling their entire social media feeds with generic "just listed, just sold" posts.

✔️ Instead, they create transformational, perspective-shifting content that helps position their services as being the #1 choice for their clients.

❌ Premium real estate brands don’t take pride in doing everything themselves - hustling from one listing to the next.

✔️ Instead, they recognize the value of automation, systems and delegation. Not just because it helps the CEO - but because of how it elevates their client's experience.

Remember…you are building a brand that’s meant to LAST. You’re building a brand that will eventually attract everything you desire into your life ✨

So let me know your answer in the comments…what’s it going to be, Walmart or Chanel?

It’s time to take FULL responsibility for your marketing ⚡⁠

⁠One of the biggest mistakes I see agents make is outsourcing before they’re ready.⁠

⁠While YES, I’m huge on delegating to stay in your zone of genius…💡⁠

⁠Hiring someone to do something for you before you know the basics is never a good idea.⁠

⁠Agents will tell me:⁠

⁠👉🏼 “Oh, I’m not worried about social media…I hired a VA to do that for me”⁠

👉🏼 Or, “I’m not a marketing person… I’ll just hire a marketing agency”⁠

👉🏼 Or, “I hired a branding company to build my messaging and marketing strategy”⁠

⁠The question I have for you is this:⁠

⁠If YOU don’t understand the principles of good marketing… how do you know that they’re doing a good job?⁠

⁠Do you know what a good job looks like? Are you able to measure it?⁠

⁠Marketing is the LIFEBLOOD of your business.⁠ You NEED to understand it... not just hope that you hired the right people who "understand" it.

⁠I don't want you to feel like you’re dependent on someone else if you want your business to survive.⁠

⁠The more you know, the more you know... 

Yes, that sounds weird, but think about it in terms of fishing.

⁠Don’t buy fish... learn how to fish... learn how to be the best fisherman in the industry and then teach someone to fish for you! 🎣⁠

⁠The more fish you buy (I think we both know - we’re talking about leads here at this point)... the more control that fisherman has over you. He actually has full control over your business. You don’t have a business without clients.⁠

Buying leads or hiring someone to generate leads for you, before you master it yourself... isn't a good idea.

⁠It makes you vulnerable in the most important aspect of reaching your goals.

⁠I know that I wouldn’t want anyone else in control of my goals…⁠

⁠Learn to fish and your business will never go hungry 💯 Who agrees?⁠

Success doesn’t come from waiting for perfection. ⁠
⁠
The secret to achieving your goals comes from having the courage to launch and learn. ⁠
⁠
So many of us spend valuable time waiting for everything to line up just right, for everything to be 100% perfect BEFORE taking action. ⁠
⁠
But it’s through the act of implementing - of actually doing the thing you set out to do and receiving valuable feedback - that builds our confidence and gets us closer to where we want to be.⁠
⁠
The truth is that waiting to be “ready” is your brain’s way of protecting you from failure, disappointment, and risk. ⁠
⁠
But trying things, failing, and figuring it out along the way is how you grow 🌱⁠
⁠
So recognize when preparation becomes a crutch. Getting valuable data doesn’t come from planning. It comes from DOING the thing. ⁠
⁠
So have the courage to put yourself out there and implement and learn to receive enough data to find the right solution. ⁠
⁠
And remember... you can’t become great without failure. The faster you accept that fact, the faster you’ll hit your goals. ⁠
⁠
Leave a “🙌🏼” in the comments if you’re done waiting for perfection and are ready to embrace a launch and learn mindset!⁠

Are you stuck in FREEZE mode? ⁠
⁠
You’ve probably heard about the common stress responses of fight or flight, but what’s even more common is the freeze reaction. ⁠
⁠
Freeze mode keeps us stagnant. It’s when we know we need to move, to change, to grow, to do something new…⁠
⁠
But we’re too overwhelmed and paralyzed to start.⁠
⁠
I see this happening a lot with agents right now. ⁠
⁠
The way we’re marketing and growing our businesses has changed drastically in the past 5 years. ⁠
⁠
Agents know they need to innovate, but they find themselves frozen in place, unable to take action. ⁠
⁠
💥 Don't get stuck in freeze mode. 💥⁠
⁠
The majority of people who go into freeze mode stay paralyzed by fear, uncertainty, and self-doubt and never learn how to adapt to move beyond that fear.⁠
⁠
But your success in real estate DEPENDS on your ability to override this default mode. ⁠
⁠
That feeling - the rush of fear or your racing heart – is keeping you stuck in place. It's your body's way of protecting you from what it perceives as a threat. ⁠
⁠
It’s your body’s automatic survival mechanism trying to keep you safe. ⁠
⁠
Getting to your next level starts with recognizing when you’re frozen and then making an effort to take action - no matter how uncomfortable it might feel. ⁠
⁠
In TLL, we show you how to think and act like a marketer. How to take action, adapt, and grow into a confident CEO. ⁠
⁠
The question is: Are you ready to unfreeze?⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

Here's how a scarcity mindset is sabotaging your business's growth 👇🏼⁠
⁠
A scarcity mindset often sounds like this: ⁠
⁠
"I can't miss his call, I need this deal so badly"⁠
⁠
"I need a vacation, but I chose to work in real estate, so this is just the name of the game!"⁠
⁠
"Other agents are getting all of the clients in my market" ⁠
⁠
"They're not my ideal client, but I really need the money, so...."⁠
⁠
You might think these thoughts are harmless, but they're actually dangerous. Here's why.⁠
⁠
What you believe is the first step to everything that you create.⁠
⁠
Beliefs trigger emotions.⁠
⁠
Emotions lead to thoughts.⁠
⁠
Thoughts create decisions.⁠
⁠
Decisions trigger actions.⁠
⁠
Actions lead to…⁠
⁠
Results. ⁠
⁠
If you see the world through a lens of scarcity, then guess what will be reflected back to you?⁠
⁠
Yep, more scarcity. ⁠
⁠
Flipping scarcity on its head isn't just a fun thought exercise. It's a non-negotiable if you're ready to scale.⁠
⁠
The first step? ⁠
⁠
Recognizing where scarcity might have a grip on you. So let me know in the comments...which one of these scarcity signs sounds familiar to you? ⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
⁠

I could’ve let my ego win.⁠
⁠
But I didn’t.⁠
⁠
I remember hiring one of my first mentors. He was only 27 at the time.⁠
⁠
I could’ve judged him based on his age.⁠
⁠
Or told myself that I had more years of business experience.⁠
⁠
Or assumed he’d just gotten lucky - that he’d just had the right cards dealt to him.⁠
⁠
But at the end of the day, I recognized:⁠
⁠
He had the experience that I didn’t have. Experience that my business *needed* to succeed.⁠
⁠
And that was all that mattered.⁠
⁠
I went all-in on his advice and didn’t look back.⁠
⁠
If you want to build a 7-figure business, ask yourself:⁠

Your 3-Part Framework To Doing LESS In Your Real Estate Business 👇🏼⁠
⁠
If you have too much on your plate right now, follow this 3-step plan.⁠
⁠
❌ ELIMINATE⁠
⁠
Assess what can be completely removed from your workload. Get rid of tasks that are time-consuming and don’t contribute to your core objectives. ⁠
⁠
💻 AUTOMATE⁠
⁠
Automation is your key to saving time and keeping things as efficient as possible. Tasks don’t always need to be done by a human. Don’t spend $30/hour paying an administrator when you could spend $20/month on software. ⁠
⁠
🤝 OUTSOURCE⁠
⁠
Not everything in your business is going to fall in your zone of genius. This is where outsourcing comes in. By delegating tasks to experts in their respective fields, you can focus on what you do best. ⁠
⁠
This is a theory that I follow from Tim Ferris, the king of efficiency and author of The 4-Hour Work Week. ⁠
⁠
This is an approach I’ve used for years so I can make time for the CEO-level tasks that matter the most, so I'm not constantly bogged down in the daily grind. ⁠
⁠
Tell me in the comments below…what’s ONE task you’re working to automate, outsource, or eliminate entirely from your business? ⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
⁠

I was in my zone of excellence selling real estate, but not my zone of genius. Let me explain…⁠
⁠
Back in 2017, my husband and I were running a successful 7-figure real estate business. On the surface, it seemed like we had it all. ⁠
⁠
But deep down, I still felt like something was missing.⁠
⁠
Everyone kept telling me how I was “killing it!” and how I was “such an inspiration”. So how come I didn’t feel like it?⁠
⁠
The truth is, I knew how to sell real estate, and I knew how to do it well.⁠
⁠
But when I thought about doing it for the next 10 years, I felt a pit in my stomach.⁠
⁠
One day, while on vacation in Hawaii the tough realization hit me hard...⁠
⁠
I didn’t want to sell real estate anymore. ⁠
⁠
My husband told me, “Jess, you're happiest when you're helping other agents become successful.” ⁠
⁠
Those were the words that helped me realize my true purpose and from there, The Listings Lab began. ⁠
⁠
✨ It takes time and some soul-searching in order to find your zone of genius. ✨⁠
⁠
Your zone of genius is where your unique talents and deepest passions converge. It’s where your authenticity shines, and your potential is limitless. ⁠
⁠
It’s not just about what you’re good at. It’s about what feels so natural to you, it almost doesn’t even feel like work.⁠
⁠
For me, it's coaching and educating. Mentorship. Content Creation. Public Speaking.⁠
⁠
It’s okay if you’re not living in your zone of genius yet - most people aren’t.⁠
⁠
But if you want to get closer, you need to start taking a good, hard look at the tasks you’re doing each day that don’t fill your cup.⁠
⁠
It’s time to step back, make changes, and delegate the things that don’t bring us joy. ⁠
⁠
Take a moment to pause and ask yourself:⁠
⁠
Is your real estate business allowing you to live in your zone of genius? Or are you too bogged down in tasks that are sucking all of your time and energy? Let me know in the comments 👇🏼⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

How to become the only choice for your ideal clients ✨⁠
⁠
If you want to become the go-to agent in your market, the one that everyone’s dying to work with…⁠
⁠
…then you HAVE to start embracing the power of omnipresent marketing.⁠
⁠
When you become omnipresent to your clients, it feels like you’re everywhere.⁠
⁠
They’re constantly becoming aware of you, again and again, through strategic well-timed marketing messages.⁠
⁠
Omnipresent marketing takes advantage of the cognitive bias called the mere exposure effect. ⁠
⁠
The mere exposure effect states that the more familiar you are with something, the closer you feel to it.⁠
⁠
When you’re repeatedly showing up for your ideal clients with relevant, well-timed messages:⁠
⁠
👉 On Instagram stories⁠
⁠
👉 In their inbox⁠
⁠
👉 On their Facebook feeds⁠
⁠
Or wherever else they’re hanging out…their desire to work with you will BUILD.⁠
⁠
After weeks or months of being exposed to your message, they’ll start to see you as the only agent for them 💥⁠
⁠
Want to learn more about harnessing the power of omnipresent marketing to attract your ideal clients online?⁠
⁠
Then be sure to download The Listings Lab Method guide in the link in the bio 🔗⁠

Going from 6 ➡️ 7 figures isn’t about working harder or doing “more”.

It’s about doing more of the right things and ruthlessly eliminating the rest.

It’s radically shifting your entire business model so that scalability is at the forefront.

Here are 3 shifts I did to make it happen.

👉🏼 MANUAL VS. AUTOMATED
One of the biggest shifts I made to create sustainably was implementing systems and automation wherever possible.

Always eliminate, automate and then delegate. Don’t pay someone $25/hour for a basic task that software could do for $25/month.

👉🏼 ATTRACTION VS. CHASING

Instead of constantly spending hours chasing new clients, start thinking about how you could get them to come to you.

If you’re in chase mode, you’ll always hit a plateau with how many potential clients you can reach. After all, there are only so many hours you can spend in a day cold-calling and prospecting.

👉🏼 SOLO AGENT VS. TEAM LEADER
The thing that took me from being a hustling agent to a 7-figure business owner wasn’t working “harder” or doubling my output.

It was by investing in people who were smarter than me. Growing a powerhouse team is so much more than just hiring an assistant. You need to start delegating outcomes.

Tell me in the comments…which one of these shifts is your BIGGEST priority right now?
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

“You’re so lucky! I wish I could do what you’re doing!”

When Yves and I first moved to the Bahamas, I got that A LOT.

While I do feel incredibly grateful to be where I am, it’s important to note:

This was always the intention. It’s not a fluke.

Our move was years in the making. I didn’t just “get lucky”. 

I didn’t just fall into the life and business that I have.

A few things that came before:

- A 3 year long abusive relationship

- Overcoming massive fears around being seen

- Trying and failing at different strategies

- Being shy to the point of serious social anxiety 

- Being broke and not knowing how I was going to pay my bills

- Leaving a business I was hugely successful in to start over because it felt right

I just made different decisions and I got tons of help. I’ve had coaches who have helped me plan out my next steps so I can get to where I am now.

So when you start telling yourself:

“Other people are so lucky!”…

Or you start comparing your chapter 1 to someone else’s chapter 20…

Just remember:

Everybody has a story. 

Everybody has faced immense hurdles to make their dreams a reality.

Rather than attributing someone’s success to mere luck, let’s recognize and honor the dedication, hard work, and perseverance that has shaped their journey ❤️

Who else thinks success is more about resilience & dedication than luck? Let me know if you agree in the comments 👇🏼
.
.
.
.
.
.

I used to really struggle with my own self-worth. I always felt like I had to be the best.⁠
⁠
I didn’t realize that being me was enough, so I was “nice” on the outside, but insanely competitive on the inside.⁠
⁠
I just wanted people to think I was amazing… because I didn’t.⁠
⁠
I started competitive swimming when I was 10. Because I was so tall for my age, I was faster than the other kids.⁠
⁠
Then they got taller too… and I had to work really hard. I had this fierce drive to win because I wanted people to see me as a winner.⁠
⁠
Then I started rowing. Again, I was fast because I was fit from swimming. But then everyone else got fit too and I had to work super hard.⁠
⁠
I always wanted to look like things came easily, but they didn’t. It followed me into adulthood too.⁠
⁠
I had bad boyfriends that I wanted people to think were wonderful.⁠
⁠
I started my real estate business thinking it would be easy and it wasn’t, but I never wanted it to seem like I was struggling.⁠
⁠
I am who I am today because of this, but I wouldn’t wish it on anyone.⁠
⁠
It’s made me get scrappy and figure things out because I didn’t want to have to outwork everyone for the rest of my life.⁠
⁠
It was tiring.⁠
⁠
This isn’t who I am anymore, but it took years of working on it and the awareness that it was happening.⁠
⁠
If my story resonates, remember, you're not alone. Embracing your true self, even when you're not leading the pack, is where true strength lies.⁠
⁠
Truly winning at life is self-acceptance, no matter what’s going on externally.⁠
⁠

Here's How To Cut Your Workload In HALF As An Agent...👇🏼⁠
⁠
I'm talking about monotasking.⁠
⁠
Monotasking - or single-tasking - is the practice of working on one task (and one task only!) at a time.⁠
⁠
In monotasking, you ONLY move on to your next task once the first one is complete.⁠
⁠
It's pretty much the exact opposite of how most agents work 😅⁠
⁠
Bouncing from task to task, answering your email one second, responding to texts the next, answering incoming calls from clients, and then quickly throwing up a quick post on social media. ⁠
⁠
So let this be your sign to STOP task switching!⁠
⁠
Here's how to eliminate task switching once and for all so you can cut hours in HALF while making more money!⁠
⁠
👉🏼 Batch your tasks. Group similar activities together to reduce time lost switching between them. ⁠
⁠
📲 Limit distractions. Turn off notifications and create a quiet workspace to enable deeper, more productive work periods.⁠
⁠
💰 Obsessively prioritize your most important money-making projects. Kick-off each day by focusing on tasks that drive the most revenue. ⁠
⁠
Time is the most finite resource we have access to. These tips will help you make sure you're making the most of it!⁠
⁠
Let me know in the comments...are you going to try monotasking? ⁠

I grew up with a really conservative dad. And all I ever wanted was to make him proud.⁣⁠
⁠
It took a long time for him to see the good in the choices I’d made in my life.⁣⁠
⁠
He knew that I’d essentially “fallen” into real estate because I didn’t know what I wanted to do with my life... so for years, he asked me when I was going to go back to school.⁣⁠
⁠
He’s a doctor and so he saw the world differently than I did.⁣⁠
⁠
He thought I should be a doctor too or a lawyer…⁣⁠
⁠
I felt misunderstood and frustrated for a long time because all I wanted was for him to be proud of me and approve of what I was doing.⁣⁠
⁠
He grew up in a strict household in Hong Kong, so my free-spiritedness (and my Mom’s too) was sometimes a lot for him.⁣⁠
⁠
One day, I was driving with him and I told him that I didn’t want to sell real estate anymore. I expected him to be disappointed…⁣⁠
⁠
I expected him to tell me to follow through with what I’d built... I thought he was only proud of me because I was making so much money.⁣⁠
⁠
His answer shocked me…⁣⁠
⁠
⁣“I’m not surprised. I’ve been waiting for you to make this decision. I’m proud of you.”⁣⁠
⁠
He went on to tell me that he’d seen the sparkle drain from me because I wasn’t doing what really lit me up.⁣⁠
⁠
He understood me so much better than I thought and his words telling me, ”I’m proud of you"...⁠
⁠
They meant more than any commission cheque, any happy client, or any contract.⁣⁠
⁠
I followed my passion. ⁠
⁠
I always knew I wanted to help people... I wanted to help agents. I wanted to help agents have more…. more freedom and more time for themselves and their families.⁣⁠
⁠
That one conversation made me feel seen and understood. ⁠
⁠
Since then, I’ve been closer to him than ever before.⁠
⁠
How many of you have sought approval from someone close to you? ⁠
⁠
Double-tap if you've been there and tell me about it in the comments.⁠

The best way to close out your day as the CEO of your real estate business👇⁠
⁠
I finish each day by journaling on how I spent my time.⁠
⁠
⁠I ask myself…⁠
⁠
⁠🔹 Did I spend my time wisely today? ⁠
⁠
⁠🔹 Were there any tasks I spent time on today that could’ve been outsourced? That could have been automated?⁠
⁠
⁠🔹 How much of my time was spent on $1000/hour tasks? ⁠
⁠
⁠Making a conscious, consistent effort to be regularly spending your time on $1000/hour tasks can be the difference between a $100k/year and a 7-figure one.⁠
⁠
⁠If I reflect on my day and I realize that I’m spending my time on tasks that could have been done by someone else…⁠
⁠
⁠I’ll discuss a plan with my team to get those tasks off my plate as soon as possible.⁠
⁠
⁠Your time and energy as a CEO is precious ⚡⁠
⁠
⁠You’re responsible for setting the vision.⁠
⁠
⁠Your team is responsible for EXECUTING that vision.⁠
⁠
⁠Remember to focus on the big picture, rather than getting bogged down in the weeds 💯⁠
